<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,999,1241]" pageId="4" pageNumber="357">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,267,999,1025]" pageId="4" pageNumber="357">Remarks.</emphasis>
As seen above, one of the features pointed out by 
<bibRefCitation author="Julio, C. E. A." box="[842,979,999,1025]" pageId="4" pageNumber="357" pagination="1 - 11" refId="ref11374" refString="Julio, C. E. A. (1997) Descricoes, sinonimia, novo status, novas combinacoes e chave para as especies brasileiras de Oxycoleus Lacordaire, 1869 (Coleoptera, Cerambycidae, Cerambycinae, Molorchini). Boletim do Museu Nacional, Zoologia, 381, 1 - 11." type="journal article" year="1997">Júlio (1997)</bibRefCitation>
to separate 
<taxonomicName authorityName="sensu Julio" authorityYear="1997" box="[1116,1222,999,1025]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Oxycoleus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="357" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="gahani">
<emphasis box="[1116,1222,999,1025]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="357">T. gahani</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Melzer" baseAuthorityYear="1933" box="[1293,1385,999,1024]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Oxycoleus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="357" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tristis">
<emphasis box="[1293,1385,999,1024]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="357">T. tristis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was the color of the prothorax. However, this feature is variable intraspecifically at least in some species of 
<taxonomicName authorityName=", Julio" authorityYear="1997" box="[1313,1430,1035,1061]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Oxycoleus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="357" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1313,1430,1035,1061]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="357">Oxycoleus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Therefore, this variation is expected to also occurs in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Nascimento &amp; Santos-Silva" authorityYear="2021" box="[781,889,1071,1096]" class="Insecta" family="Lycidae" genus="Wappesia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="357" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[781,889,1071,1096]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="357">Wappesia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. It is probable that 
<bibRefCitation author="Melzer, J." box="[1123,1287,1071,1097]" pageId="4" pageNumber="357" pagination="367 - 382" refId="ref11752" refString="Melzer, J. (1933) Cerambycideos neotropicos, novos ou pouco conhecidos. Revista de Entomologia, 3 (3), 367 - 382." type="journal article" year="1933">Melzer (1933)</bibRefCitation>
was correct: 
<taxonomicName box="[151,366,1107,1133]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Tethlimmena" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="357" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tristis">
<emphasis box="[151,366,1107,1133]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="357">Tethlimmena tristis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
being just a chromatic variation of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Gounelle" authorityYear="1911" box="[765,994,1107,1133]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Tethlimmena" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="357" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="gahani">
<emphasis box="[765,994,1107,1133]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="357">Tethlimmena gahani</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. See remarks on 
<taxonomicName box="[1187,1286,1107,1132]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Tethlimmena" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="357" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tristis">
<emphasis box="[1187,1286,1107,1132]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="357">W. tristis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The male illustrated by 
<bibRefCitation author="Julio, C. E. A." box="[290,426,1143,1169]" pageId="4" pageNumber="357" pagination="1 - 11" refId="ref11374" refString="Julio, C. E. A. (1997) Descricoes, sinonimia, novo status, novas combinacoes e chave para as especies brasileiras de Oxycoleus Lacordaire, 1869 (Coleoptera, Cerambycidae, Cerambycinae, Molorchini). Boletim do Museu Nacional, Zoologia, 381, 1 - 11." type="journal article" year="1997">Júlio (1997)</bibRefCitation>
has the antennae distinctly longer than in the 
<typeStatus box="[940,1038,1143,1169]" pageId="4" pageNumber="357">holotype</typeStatus>
male of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Zajciw" authorityYear="1964" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Merionoeda" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="357" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="latipennis" subGenus="Merionoeda">
<emphasis box="[1137,1274,1143,1169]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="357">Merionoeda</emphasis>
(
<emphasis box="[1290,1427,1143,1169]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="357">Merionoeda</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis box="[151,261,1179,1205]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="357">latipennis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and also than in the male of 
<taxonomicName box="[609,710,1179,1204]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Tethlimmena" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="357" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tristis">
<emphasis box="[609,710,1179,1204]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="357">W. tristis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[727,797,1179,1205]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–4. 1" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1681,1705]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,181,1655]" captionTargetId="figure-24@2.[151,1436,179,1655]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1–4. 1) Tethlimmena obscurus (Júlio, 1997), dorsal habitus, by Steven W. Lingafelter. 2–3) Wappesia tristis (Melzer, 1933): 2) Holotype female from Brazil (Santa Catarina), dorsal habitus; 3) Male from Brazil (Minas Gerais), dorsal habitus. 4) Tethlimmena aliena Bates, 1872, male from Costa Rica (Limón), dorsal habitus." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5635853" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5635853/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="357">Fig. 3</figureCitation>
). This may reinforce that 
<taxonomicName authority="sensu Julio (1997)" authorityName="sensu Julio" authorityYear="1997" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Oxycoleus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="357" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="gahani">
<emphasis box="[1098,1372,1179,1205]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="357">Oxycoleus gahani sensu</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Julio, C. E. A." pageId="4" pageNumber="357" pagination="1 - 11" refId="ref11374" refString="Julio, C. E. A. (1997) Descricoes, sinonimia, novo status, novas combinacoes e chave para as especies brasileiras de Oxycoleus Lacordaire, 1869 (Coleoptera, Cerambycidae, Cerambycinae, Molorchini). Boletim do Museu Nacional, Zoologia, 381, 1 - 11." type="journal article" year="1997">Júlio (1997)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
belongs to a different species.
</paragraph>
